---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

export const prerender = true;
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Workflows | GoldShore"
  description="How GoldShore engagements run from intake through operational delivery."
>
  <section class="gs-section gs-blueprint-bg gs-section--padded">
    <div class="gs-container">
      <h1>Engagement Workflows</h1>
      <p>
        Every engagement follows a transparent operating rhythm so teams know
        what happens next, what artifacts are produced, and how risk is reduced.
      </p>

      <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2" style="margin-top:1rem;">
        <article class="gs-card">
          <h2>1) Qualification &amp; context</h2>
          <p>
            Start with role-based intake to capture industry, stack, timeline,
            and operational constraints.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Visitor profile + goals</li>
            <li>Critical systems inventory</li>
            <li>Timeline and change window</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="gs-card">
          <h2>2) Initial architecture brief</h2>
          <p>
            We produce a lightweight engagement brief that maps outcomes,
            dependencies, and first sprint milestones.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Service bundle recommendation</li>
            <li>Week 1 deliverables</li>
            <li>30/60/90 day operating plan</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="gs-card">
          <h2>3) Secure execution</h2>
          <p>
            Delivery runs through hardened change controls, observability, and
            resilience validation.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Change review checkpoints</li>
            <li>Incident-response readiness</li>
            <li>Operational dashboard reporting</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="gs-card">
          <h2>4) Hand-off &amp; operator enablement</h2>
          <p>
            Teams leave with clear runbooks, visibility controls, and a
            sustainment cadence.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Runbooks and ownership map</li>
            <li>Security controls baseline</li>
            <li>Next-quarter roadmap options</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>

      <p style="margin-top:1.5rem;">
        <a class="gs-button gs-button-solid" href="/intake">Launch guided intake</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
